TestCaseStatusSummary.TestCaseResults: A clinical document can be revised, and a new version of the document is created.

TestCases.Name: 1941-Document Revisioning
TestCases.Objective: The objective is to verify that a clinical document can be revised, and a new version of the document is created.
TestCases.Acceptance: A clinical document can be revised, and a new version of the document is created.

Steps.Title: Given I am logged in to AODocs as 'Library Contributor' role with 'Test User Eight 8'
Steps.Description: Log in as the Library Contributor: 'Test User Eight 8'.
Steps.ExpectedResult: Login is successful for 'Test User Eight 8'.
Steps.ActualResult: Login is successful for 'Test User Eight 8'.

Steps.Title: When I search for the library 'Galvani - Clinical library' and click on it
Steps.Description: Search for the library 'Galvani - Clinical library' and click on it.
Steps.ExpectedResult: User is navigated to 'Galvani - Clinical library' page.
Steps.ActualResult: User is navigated to 'Galvani - Clinical library' page.

Steps.Title: When I create a clinical document with following information and store title 'DocumentName' and 'DocumentNo' and 'DocumentWorkFlowState':
Steps.Description: Enter the following field values: Library name = Galvani - Clinical library; Document Class = Clinical documents; Title = xLMTestDoc01; Type = Data Management; Blinding = Blinded content; Study = GAL1040; Deliverable Milestone = End of study; Indication = Rheumatoid Arthritis; Regulatory compliance = Non GxP; Archival Date = Next Year’s Date; Clinical Manager = test-user-8@xlm.aodocs.net; Clinical Reviewers1 = test-user-6@xlm.aodocs.net; Clinical Reviewers2 = test-user-8@xlm.aodocs.net; Clinical Uploaders = test-user-5@xlm.aodocs.net; Blinded Viewer = test-user-9@xlm.aodocs.net; Archived viewer = test-user-6@xlm.aodocs.net.
Steps.ExpectedResult: Document is in 'New clinical document' state.
Steps.ActualResult: Document is in 'New clinical document' state.

Steps.Title: When I click on workflow and select 'Send for review' from drop-down list and current workflow state is 'New clinical document'
Steps.Description: Navigate to the 'New clinical document' workflow state button and click on : 'Send for review'.
Steps.ExpectedResult: 'Perform work flow action' window is popped-up.
Steps.ActualResult: 'Perform work flow action' window is popped-up.

Steps.Title: When I enter the comment 'Test' and submit then verify the state changed as 'In-Review'
Steps.Description: Leave a comment 'Test' and click on submit.
Steps.ExpectedResult: The Clinical document is transitioned to 'In-Review' workflow state.
Steps.ActualResult: The Clinical document is transitioned to 'In-Review' workflow state.

Steps.Title: When I click on workflow and select 'Archive' from drop-down list and click on submit with comment 'Test' and see 'Archived' workflow state
Steps.Description: Click on the Workflow icon and select 'Archive'.Click on 'Submit' on the 'Perform work flow action' window. Verify that the workflow state is displayed as 'Archived'.
Steps.ExpectedResult: The workflow state of the clinical document is displayed as 'Archived'.
Steps.ActualResult: The workflow state of the clinical document is displayed as 'Archived'.

Steps.Title: When I click on workflow and select 'Create a new version' from drop-down list and click on submit with comment 'Test' and see 'Clinical document under revision' workflow state
